00:22:55,047 --> 00:22:58,567
He didn't even reply to a single letter.

253
00:22:58,567 --> 00:23:01,477
I hated him so much for it.

254
00:23:01,477 --> 00:23:07,137
After that, I had forgotten about him.

255
00:23:08,087 --> 00:23:13,497
He... He, here...

256
00:23:18,197 --> 00:23:19,617
It's not your fault.

257
00:23:19,617 --> 00:23:24,207
Why didn't I know? He was without a pair of shoes,

258
00:23:24,207 --> 00:23:27,347
and he was standing there when the waves were coming.

259
00:23:27,347 --> 00:23:30,107
His hair was not cut properly,

260
00:23:30,107 --> 00:23:33,467
and his body was covered with bruises.

261
00:23:33,467 --> 00:23:36,257
It's not your fault.

262
00:23:36,257 --> 00:23:39,337
No. It's my fault.

263
00:23:39,337 --> 00:23:42,897
Those were all signs.

264
00:23:42,897 --> 00:23:46,217
How did I not realize?

265
00:23:47,037 --> 00:23:50,397
He promised me that he would be an adult for sure.

266
00:23:50,397 --> 00:23:55,457
I laughed at him and teased him for it.

267
00:23:55,457 --> 00:24:00,197
I told him growing up was a natural thing for kids and he didn't have to try to be one.

268
00:24:00,197 --> 00:24:04,097
But for him...

269
00:24:37,667 --> 00:24:40,107
Don't blame yourself.

270
00:24:40,107 --> 00:24:44,567
His fate was only up to that point.

271
00:24:44,567 --> 00:24:50,597
Fate? That's simple and brutal.

272
00:24:51,287 --> 00:24:54,947
He must have always been scared all his life.

273
00:24:54,947 --> 00:25:01,347
Until the last moment, how frighting must it have been?

274
00:25:01,347 --> 00:25:04,317
I feel like I'm going to go crazy right now.

275
00:25:06,637 --> 00:25:08,347
Fate?

276
00:25:09,457 --> 00:25:15,317
No, he... Seong Woo... that kid,

277
00:25:18,127 --> 00:25:23,917
probably... thought of you at the end.

278
00:25:23,917 --> 00:25:28,697
In the end, up until his last moment.

279
00:25:28,697 --> 00:25:33,387
How do you know that?

280
00:25:36,437 --> 00:25:39,647
I just think it was probably like that.

281
00:25:39,647 --> 00:25:43,867
Because you were probably the one and only good memory he had,

282
00:25:43,867 --> 00:25:48,757
he would have thought of you. Definitely.

283
00:25:49,967 --> 00:25:51,877
Really?

284
00:25:51,877 --> 00:25:56,017
He knows that you are the only person who remembers him.

285
00:25:57,587 --> 00:25:59,957
He's probably really thankful.

286
00:26:28,507 --> 00:26:32,037
Seong Woo, I'm sorry I'm here so late.

287
00:26:32,037 --> 00:26:37,737
I didn't know. I can't even imagine what happened. I'm so...

288
00:26:37,737 --> 00:26:39,877
♫  A constant break  ♫

289
00:26:39,877 --> 00:26:43,437
I'm really sorry.

290
00:26:43,437 --> 00:26:49,607
♫  Our minds belong to theirs who risk  ♫

291
00:26:49,607 --> 00:26:51,677
♫  To those who seek  ♫

292
00:26:51,677 --> 00:26:57,297
Why aren't you praying? Try asking God, that you like so much,

293
00:26:57,297 --> 00:27:03,497
why He made a 12-year-old's life so painful.

294
00:27:03,497 --> 00:27:10,717
If there really is a god, does He have to be like this to the end?

295
00:27:10,717 --> 00:27:14,397
♫  I don't know if I can anymore  ♫

296
00:27:14,397 --> 00:27:17,337
God couldn't have left him alone like that.

297
00:27:17,337 --> 00:27:21,377
I know, right?

298
00:27:21,377 --> 00:27:26,007
Why was God so harsh on him?

